              I got me a new (old) bicycle today!<BR><BR><IMG SRC="http://milliron.org/hosted/DSC_0102.jpg">   <BR><BR>It's a ten or eleven year old Trek 520. It has a steel frame and I guess it's a touring bike. I took the rear rack off and swapped the 38s for 23s. Though, I like the idea of doing a multi day self supported bike ride. Sounds fun.<BR><BR>I know nothing about road bikes but it seems really comfortable, is in excellent condition, shifts smoothly and was cheap.  Can't wait to give it a workout tomorrow morning.<BR><BR>Oh and here are some other bike pics while I'm at it.  Sort of as a continuation to this <a href="http://episteme.arstechnica.com/eve/forums/a/tpc/f/34709834/m/424001968831/inc/1" target="_blank">thread</a>.<BR><BR><IMG SRC="http://milliron.org/hosted/DSC_0109.jpg">   <BR><BR>My Superlight.<BR><BR><IMG SRC="http://milliron.org/hosted/DSC_0107.jpg">   <BR><BR><a href="http://www.dinottelighting.com/LED_bike_lights/600l-li-4c.htm" target="_blank">Dinotte 600L</a> light & battery, Garmin Edge 305 gps.<BR><BR><IMG SRC="http://milliron.org/hosted/500.png">   <BR><BR>Haven't ridden in the last week and a half because of my wisdom teeth extraction.  Yuck.<BR><BR><IMG SRC="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2192/2207907112_c959ef53ce_o.jpg"> 

              

              
              
            </div>
